snippets.title: dataproc createAutoscalingPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Creates new autoscaling policy.

snippets.title: dataproc updateAutoscalingPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Updates (replaces) autoscaling policy. Disabled check for update_mask, because all updates will be full replacements.

snippets.title: dataproc getAutoscalingPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves autoscaling policy.

snippets.title: dataproc listAutoscalingPolicies Sample
snippets.description: Lists autoscaling policies in the project.

snippets.title: dataproc deleteAutoscalingPolicy Sample
snippets.description: Deletes an autoscaling policy. It is an error to delete an autoscaling policy that is in use by one or more clusters.

snippets.title: dataproc createBatch Sample
snippets.description: Creates a batch workload that executes asynchronously.

snippets.title: dataproc getBatch Sample
snippets.description: Gets the batch workload resource representation.

snippets.title: dataproc listBatches Sample
snippets.description: Lists batch workloads.

snippets.title: dataproc deleteBatch Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the batch workload resource. If the batch is not in terminal state, the delete fails and the response returns `FAILED_PRECONDITION`.

snippets.title: dataproc createCluster Sample
snippets.description: Creates a cluster in a project. The returned [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [ClusterOperationMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#clusteroperationmetadata).

snippets.title: dataproc updateCluster Sample
snippets.description: Updates a cluster in a project. The returned [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [ClusterOperationMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#clusteroperationmetadata). The cluster must be in a [`RUNNING`][google.cloud.dataproc.v1.ClusterStatus.State] state or an error is returned.

snippets.title: dataproc stopCluster Sample
snippets.description: Stops a cluster in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc startCluster Sample
snippets.description: Starts a cluster in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc deleteCluster Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a cluster in a project. The returned [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [ClusterOperationMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#clusteroperationmetadata).

snippets.title: dataproc getCluster Sample
snippets.description: Gets the resource representation for a cluster in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc listClusters Sample
snippets.description: Lists all regions/{region}/clusters in a project alphabetically.

snippets.title: dataproc diagnoseCluster Sample
snippets.description: Gets cluster diagnostic information. The returned [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [ClusterOperationMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#clusteroperationmetadata). After the operation completes, [Operation.response][google.longrunning.Operation.response] contains [DiagnoseClusterResults](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#diagnoseclusterresults).

snippets.title: dataproc submitJob Sample
snippets.description: Submits a job to a cluster.

snippets.title: dataproc submitJobAsOperation Sample
snippets.description: Submits job to a cluster.

snippets.title: dataproc getJob Sample
snippets.description: Gets the resource representation for a job in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc listJobs Sample
snippets.description: Lists regions/{region}/jobs in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc updateJob Sample
snippets.description: Updates a job in a project.

snippets.title: dataproc cancelJob Sample
snippets.description: Starts a job cancellation request. To access the job resource after cancellation, call [regions/{region}/jobs.list](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.regions.jobs/list) or [regions/{region}/jobs.get](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.regions.jobs/get).

snippets.title: dataproc deleteJob Sample
snippets.description: Deletes the job from the project. If the job is active, the delete fails, and the response returns `FAILED_PRECONDITION`.

snippets.title: dataproc createWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Creates new workflow template.

snippets.title: dataproc getWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Retrieves the latest workflow template. Can retrieve previously instantiated template by specifying optional version parameter.

snippets.title: dataproc instantiateWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Instantiates a template and begins execution. The returned Operation can be used to track execution of workflow by polling [operations.get][google.longrunning.Operations.GetOperation]. The Operation will complete when entire workflow is finished. The running workflow can be aborted via [operations.cancel][google.longrunning.Operations.CancelOperation]. This will cause any inflight jobs to be cancelled and workflow-owned clusters to be deleted. The [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [WorkflowMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#workflowmetadata). Also see [Using WorkflowMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/concepts/workflows/debugging#using_workflowmetadata). On successful completion, [Operation.response][google.longrunning.Operation.response] will be [Empty][google.protobuf.Empty].

snippets.title: dataproc instantiateInlineWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Instantiates a template and begins execution. This method is equivalent to executing the sequence [CreateWorkflowTemplate][google.cloud.dataproc.v1.WorkflowTemplateService.CreateWorkflowTemplate], [InstantiateWorkflowTemplate][google.cloud.dataproc.v1.WorkflowTemplateService.InstantiateWorkflowTemplate], [DeleteWorkflowTemplate][google.cloud.dataproc.v1.WorkflowTemplateService.DeleteWorkflowTemplate]. The returned Operation can be used to track execution of workflow by polling [operations.get][google.longrunning.Operations.GetOperation]. The Operation will complete when entire workflow is finished. The running workflow can be aborted via [operations.cancel][google.longrunning.Operations.CancelOperation]. This will cause any inflight jobs to be cancelled and workflow-owned clusters to be deleted. The [Operation.metadata][google.longrunning.Operation.metadata] will be [WorkflowMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/reference/rpc/google.cloud.dataproc.v1#workflowmetadata). Also see [Using WorkflowMetadata](https://cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/concepts/workflows/debugging#using_workflowmetadata). On successful completion, [Operation.response][google.longrunning.Operation.response] will be [Empty][google.protobuf.Empty].

snippets.title: dataproc updateWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Updates (replaces) workflow template. The updated template must contain version that matches the current server version.

snippets.title: dataproc listWorkflowTemplates Sample
snippets.description: Lists workflows that match the specified filter in the request.

snippets.title: dataproc deleteWorkflowTemplate Sample
snippets.description: Deletes a workflow template. It does not cancel in-progress workflows.
